  </td>
  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Colony ships allow you to colonize other planets, found=
ing
  new worlds for your empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>The ship is consumed when a new colony is established. =
The resources
  from the ship are used to give the colony a kickstart.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>While most ships are built at space ports, Colony ships=
 can
  only be built at colonies. The colony must also have a population of at l=
east
  500 million before it is able to build a colony ship. When the colony shi=
p is
  built, it takes population from the colony &#8211; the amount might be
  anywhere from 30 million to 100 million, depending on the colonization mo=
dule
  used. This population will be used to colonize the new planet.<o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Colony ships take a long time to build. Producing a ship
  that establishes a new colony is a major undertaking. When choosing where=
 to
  build a new colony ship, consider the population level and development of=
 the
  build colony. Colonies with larger populations and higher development lev=
els
  will build new colony ships faster than other colonies.<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>At the start of the game you can only colonize the nati=
ve
  planet type of your race. But as your research uncovers new technology you
  can progressively colonize other types of planets.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>However you can always colonize planets where there is =
an
  existing independent alien population, regardless of the type of planet. =
In
  these situations the preexisting population may decide to resist your
  colonization attempt, with the loss of your colony ship.<o:p></o:p></span=
></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>To cycle through all your colony ships use the Cycle Co=
lony
  and Exploration Ships button, or use the 'X' key.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
